This paper introduces a new logical notion, which is relevant to several areas of computer science. The study of partial entailment is primarily concerned with logical reasoning and inference, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). However, the paper also discusses the potential application of partial entailments in reasoning about rational agents, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational properties of partial entailments, which is relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper formalizes partial entailments using an extended notion of prime implicant, which is relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
